    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/technical-standards-and-regulations-directive-98-34-a-guide"/>
    <title>Technical Standards and Regulations Directive 98/34: a guide</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Guide to the Technical Standards and Regulations Directive 98/34. The Directive sets up a legal mechanism that requests member states to notify to the European Commission, and to the other Members, of their technical regulations, at a draft stage. At this stage amendments can still be introduced and a standstill period of 3 months observed before the adoption of the draft technical regulation (except for urgent, fiscal and financial measures).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
